wiki.summary: Unortheta is the debut album by Icelandic black/death metal band ZHRINE. The album received positive reviews from critics, with Decibel naming it 'Best New Noise', writing that "With their debut LP, Unortheta, the Reykjavík-based quartet have conjured a churning black/death vortex that takes the disgusting atonality of avant-garders like Blut Aus Nord, melds it with the oppressively frigid atmosphere of Svartidauði (guitarist Nökkvi Gylfason is a member), and folds in fetid layers of doom and psychedelia for good measure." Read more on Last.fm.
